data.enText: a long straight part with a weight at the end that moves regularly from side to side to control the movement of a clock

data.chText: 教育界又恢复了传统教学法。
data.enText: In education, the pendulum has swung back to traditional teaching methods.

simple_means.memory_skill: pend 悬挂 + ulum 表物 → 悬摆着的东西 → 钟摆

tr: an apparatus consisting of an object mounted so that it swings freely under the influence of gravity

value.def: The pendulum of a clock is a rod with a weight at the end which swings from side to side in order to make the clock work.
You can use the idea of a pendulum and the way it swings regularly as a way of talking about regular changes in a situation or in people's opinions.

example.ex: The pendulum has swung back and the American car companies have made dramatic advances in safety...
example.tran: 三十年河东，三十年河西，美国汽车公司在安全方面已经取得了巨大进步。

example.ex: The political pendulum has swung in favour of the liberals.
example.tran: 政治形势转而对自由主义者有利。

value.tran: （局势意见等的）摇摆不定，变化不定
